{{> profile-secondary-nav}}

<div class="container">

  <hgroup>
    <h1>Authenticated Tokens</h1>
  </hgroup>

  <p class="notice">
    When you log into npm via the Command Line Interface (CLI), an authentication token is created in your <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/files/npmrc">.npmrc</a> file. This authentication token is used in lieu of a username/password combination, thus enabling anyone with access to that token the ability to be your user and do things such as publish and unpublish packages. When you delete a token, your username is immediately logged out from the instance using the .npmrc with that token, and you will have to run `npm login` again.
  </p>

  <table class="subscriptions">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Token</th>
        <th>Created</th>
        <th>Delete</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {{#each tokens}}
        <tr>
          <td>{{token}}</td>
          <td data-date="{{created}}" data-date-format="%B %e %Y">
            {{created}}
          </td>
          <td>
            <form method="POST" id="token-delete-{{@index}}" action="/settings/token/{{token}}">
              {{#with ../this}}
              {{> form_security }}
              {{/with}}
              <input type="hidden" name="updateType" value="deleteToken" />
              <button type="submit" class="icon-x"><span class="a11y-only">Delete Token {{token}}</span></button>
            </form>
          </td>
        </tr>
      {{else}}
        <tr>
          <td colspan=2>You are not logged in to any cli sessions.<td>
        </tr>
      {{/each}}
    </tbody>
  </table>

</div>